<paragraph id="8BDC3E19914F7765FF4C7C98DF18F978" blockId="45.[151,1436,1594,2020]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B917E20B914F7765FF4C7C98DB59F910" box="[198,325,1675,1700]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished by olivaceous coloration and male proctiger with distal margin triangularly emarginated (
<figureCitation id="1358229C914F7765FEBD7CA1DBB9F978" box="[311,421,1714,1740]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="46.[151,255,1668,1692]" captionTargetBox="[280,1306,477,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-219@46.[280,1307,477,1654]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 25. Ventral, lateral, and dorsal views of pygophore of species of Epitoxicoris. A-C. E. allisonae sp. nov., D-F. E. trimaculatus sp. nov.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088774" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088774/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 25A</figureCitation>
). In females the posterior margin of ninth gonocoxae is smoothly convex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC3E19914F7765FF4C7CC8DB7DF820" blockId="45.[151,1436,1594,2020]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B917E20B914F7765FF4C7CC8DB44F940" box="[198,344,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Description.</emphasis>
Body 2X longer than broad (
<figureCitation id="1358229C914F7765FD3F7CC9D90FF940" box="[693,787,1754,1780]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[298,1259,1009,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-236@7.[277,1315,978,1901]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Anchises, Babylas, Epitoxicoris, and Elemana species, habitus. A. A. parvulus (Westwood), B. B. bihamatus, C. Ep. allisonae sp. nov., D. Ep. trimaculatus sp. nov., E. El. propria Distant." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088724" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088724/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Anteroventral margin of bucculae strongly produced dorsally. Labium elongate; segment ratios 1:1.6:1.6:1. Pronotum with anterolateral margins subentire, some vague crenulations anteriorly; anterolateral margins slightly carinate. Lateral margins of scutellum constricted distally before expanding into flattened disc. Mesosternum slightly sulcate. Metafemora with row of small ventral tubercles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC3E19914F7766FF4C7DB0D8EEFEB6" blockId="45.[151,1436,1594,2020]" lastBlockId="46.[151,1436,152,418]" lastPageId="46" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B917E20B914F7765FF4C7DB0DB13F808" box="[198,271,1955,1980]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Color.</emphasis>
Ground color straminous with rusty, black, and pale green mottling. Antennal segments I–II dorsolaterally testaceous; segments III–IV testaceous throughout. Posterior half of pronotum dark with median pale band. Anterolateral excavations of scutellum black. Membrane of forewing clear to dusky. Labium straminous to testaceous; apical portion of 4th segment castaneous. Venter of abdomen pale with dark spiracles. Legs pale green; tubercles of profemora testaceous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC3E19914C7766FF4C7B03DAE1FE16" blockId="46.[151,1436,152,418]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B917E20B914C7766FF4C7B03DB16FE9D" box="[198,266,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Male.</emphasis>
Ventral margin of pygophore trilobed, middle lobe smaller than laterals (
<figureCitation id="1358229C914C7766FBF37B03DEF5FE9E" box="[1145,1257,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="46.[151,255,1668,1692]" captionTargetBox="[280,1306,477,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-219@46.[280,1307,477,1654]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 25. Ventral, lateral, and dorsal views of pygophore of species of Epitoxicoris. A-C. E. allisonae sp. nov., D-F. E. trimaculatus sp. nov.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088774" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088774/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 25A</figureCitation>
). Basal sclerite of proctiger elongate, rectangular, over half length of dorsolateral lobes (
<figureCitation id="1358229C914C7766FC707B2BDE74FEE6" box="[1018,1128,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="46.[151,255,1668,1692]" captionTargetBox="[280,1306,477,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-219@46.[280,1307,477,1654]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 25. Ventral, lateral, and dorsal views of pygophore of species of Epitoxicoris. A-C. E. allisonae sp. nov., D-F. E. trimaculatus sp. nov.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088774" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088774/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 25C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger apically emarginate with triangular emargination (
<figureCitation id="1358229C914C7766FDD87B73D8DFFECE" box="[594,707,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="46.[151,255,1668,1692]" captionTargetBox="[280,1306,477,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-219@46.[280,1307,477,1654]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 25. Ventral, lateral, and dorsal views of pygophore of species of Epitoxicoris. A-C. E. allisonae sp. nov., D-F. E. trimaculatus sp. nov.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088774" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088774/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 25A</figureCitation>
). Tubercle of medial penile plates on proximal margin (
<figureCitation id="1358229C914C7766FAE77B73DAECFE16" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="47.[151,255,1047,1071]" captionTargetBox="[273,1321,469,1022]" captionTargetId="figure-144@47.[273,1321,469,1031]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 26. Ventral and lateral views of aedeagus and external female genitalia of species of A-C. E. allisonae sp. nov., D-F. E. trimaculatus sp. nov.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088776" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088776/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 26A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1C6E91914C7766FF1D7C97DB87F90B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088774" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5088774" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088774/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" startId="46.[151,255,1668,1692]" targetBox="[280,1306,477,1644]" targetPageId="46">
